From 9d16d9abef986c7fe734a69e3ba634ac1b0ba7b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adam McGreggor <adam@adamamyl.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 22:08:55 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat(embed): readonly mode, postMessage handshake, origin
 validation

Adds embed mode for use as a trusted iframe:
- ?embed=true hides header and enables postMessage API
- ?readonly=true suppresses click-to-pin (view-only)
- ?marker=lat,lon pre-sets a pin on load
- resize() on load fixes WebGL green-box in iframe context

Handshake: parent sends emf-embed-init from its origin, map validates
origin against EMBED_ALLOWED_ORIGINS (production) or *.*.internal
wildcard (local dev), then activates click-to-pin and emf-marker/emf-view
postMessage reporting.

Uses boolean embedActivated flag (not { once: true }) so spurious
messages from extensions/Workbox/URLHash don't consume the listener.

